<feed> <https://w3id.org/tree#member> <#3d6c07e564d893f5616bc6bbee813c57>.
<#3d6c07e564d893f5616bc6bbee813c57> a <https://www.w3.org/ns/activitystreams#Create>;
    <https://www.w3.org/ns/activitystreams#object> <https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.17571537>;
    <https://www.w3.org/ns/activitystreams#published> "2026-04-16T06:38:21.945Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime>.
<#3d6c07e564d893f5616bc6bbee813c57> {
<https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.17571537> <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#keyword> "Viking Age"@en, "Runverket"@en, "Runestone"@en, "Rune stone"@en, "Runsten"@en, "Runor"@en, "Runes"@en, "Tidigkristna gravmonument"@en, "Runinskrifter"@en, "Runic inscriptions"@en, "Early Christian grave monument"@en, "11th century"@en, "Late Viking Age"@en, "Early Middle Age"@en, "Ög 2"@en, "Ög 5"@en, "Ög 6"@en, "Ög 240"@en, "Ög 241"@en, "Ög Hov12;21"@en, "Ög Hov14;22"@en, "Ög Hov15;22"@en, "Sm 124"@en, "Sm 125"@en, "Östergötland"@en, "Orlunda"@en, "Hov"@en, "Visingsö"@en;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#qualifiedAttribution> _:b0__5434.
_:b0__5434 <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#hadRole> <http://inspire.ec.europa.eu/metadata-codelist/ResponsiblePartyRole/principalInvestigator>;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#agent> <https://admin.dataportal.se/store/818/resource/e0926778acd5f41c66a95651951abd92>;
    a <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Attribution>.
<https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.17571537> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/accessRights> <http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/access-right/PUBLIC>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/publisher> <http://dataportal.se/organisation/SE2021001090>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> "3D-scans of runestones and Early Christian grave monuments from Östergötland and Småland.\n\nThis dataset includes 3D-models of 11th century Early Christian grave monuments 3D-scanned for research. The study focussed on analysis of the runic inscriptions and ornament, therefor only the inscription surfaces have been scanned.\n\nThe data was collected within a study included in the thesis project by Cecilia Ljung. Results of analysis have been published by Cecilia Ljung in her doctiral thesis \"Under runristad häll: Tidigkristna gravmonument i 1000-talets Sverige\" (2016, pp. 82-83) (see related publications).\n\nThe signum Ög + number is an ID-code used in the record of runic inscriptions kept by Runverket at the Swedish National Heritage Board. The signum originates in the corpus publication Sveriges runinskrifter and other publications and reports, and is used in most publications and web-based resources. It is the key to find further references on a specific runic inscription and the object carrying it.\n\nThe sigla have been complemented by other identifiers, i.e. names and catalogue numbers in Ljung 2016.\n\nLjung, Cecilia (2016). Under runristad häll [2]. Katalog över tidigkristna gravmonument. Stockholm.\n\nÖg + nr = Runic inscription in Östergötlands runinskrifter. Brate, Erik (ed.) (1911-1918). Sveriges runinskrifter Bd 2. Stockholm : Almqvist & Wiksell international.\n\nÖg Hov + nr = Runic inscription in Stenfynden i Hovs kyrka. Jansson, Sven B. F. (1962). Filologiskt arkiv 9.\n\nÖg [+ letters] + nr = Runic inscription in the research platform Runor, runor.raa.se\n\nThe carving surfaces were recorded in 2008 with optical 3D-scanner ATOS II from GOM, measuring volume 350x280x280mm, measuring point distance 0.27 mm, and are here provided in STL-format. The scanning was made by Laila Kitzler Åhfeldt."@en;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#distribution> <https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.17571537#distribution>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/issued> "2025-11-10T00:00:00Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime>;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#landingPage> <https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.17571537>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/modified> "2025-11-14T00:00:00Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/title> "3D-data Tidigkristna gravmonument Östergötland och Småland\n3D-data Early Christian grave monuments in Östergötland and Småland"@en;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#theme> <http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/data-theme/EDUC>;
    a <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#Dataset>
}

