<https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8233989> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/accessRights> <http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/access-right/PUBLIC>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/publisher> <http://dataportal.se/organisation/SE2021002320>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> "Electronic supplement for the article Developers Talking About Code Quality\n\nPlease refer to the following paper when you cite/use this data:\n\nJ. Börstler, K.E. Bennin, S. Hooshangi, J. Jeuring, H. Keuning, C. Kleiner, B. MacKellar, R. Duran, H. Störrle, D. Toll, J van Assema. Developers Talking About Code Quality. Empirical Software Engineering, 2023.\nhttps://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/s10664-023-10381-0\n\nOverview of the electronic supplement (sorted according to file names)\n\n\t\nThe data\n\t\n\n\t\t\ndata_all-except-Q4.xlsx\n\t\tThe original cleaned data for Questions Q1-Q3 and Q5-Q11.\n\t\t\ndata_Q4 assertions.xlsx\n\t\tThe \"assertions\" which are based on the transcripts of Q4.\n\t\n\t\n\t\nThe information provided to study participants\n\t\n\n\t\t\nparticipants_consent-form_EN.pdf\n\t\tThe consent form the participants signed (English version, interviewees received a copy on request).\n\t\t\nparticipants_interview-info.pdf\n\t\tThe information sheet that was handed out for recruiting interview participants (they could keep this form).\n\t\n\t\n\t\nThe study design and guidelines\n\t\n\n\t\t\nstudy-design_coding-guide_birds-eye-summaries.pdf\n\t\tThe guidelines for coding the transcripts of Q4 into \"assertions\" (which we call \"birds-eye summaries\" in these guidelines).\n\t\t\nstudy-design_main.pdf\n\t\tThe main study guide comprising (among others) a detailed interview script.\n\t\t\nstudy-design_transcription.pdf\n\t\tThe guidelines used for transcribing Q4."@en;
    a <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#Dataset>
}

